DataElement.preferredDefinition: A non-proprietary, third generation modelling language. The Unified Modeling Language is an open method used to specify, visualise, construct and document the artifacts of an object-oriented software-intensive system under development. The UML represents a compilation of "best engineering practices" which have proven successful in modelling large, complex systems.:A grouping of things based on shared common attributes.:A description of the affiliation between two occurrences of Object Classes.:A registry item for which administrative information is recorded in an Administration Record.:Data about data; information that describes another set of data._Where something is available or from where it originates.:A grouping of things based on shared common attributes.:The usual or expected function of something; the part something plays in an action or event.:The words or language units by which a thing is known._Generic value domain for a java datatype that is a class that represents character strings.
